// 11.605 — 🛡️ CVE patch — postcss `^8.5.10` override added to `pnpm.overrides`. `pnpm audit --prod` flagged GHSA-qx2v-qp2m-jg93 (PostCSS XSS via unescaped `</style>` in CSS Stringify Output, severity moderate). Path: `.>next>postcss` — Next 16.2.4 bundles the vulnerable version transitively. Threat: attacker controlling CSS rendered through PostCSS stringify could inject `</style><script>...</script>` to escape style context. Practical impact for scc: low — public marketing site doesn't render user-controlled CSS — but CVE flags hit CI scanners + npm-audit reports. Sister inv v379.605 + glw v10.605 same-push. Post-fix `pnpm audit --prod` returns `No known vulnerabilities found`. Lockfile diff small. tsc clean.
// 11.505 — 🔒 Defense-in-depth: NODE_ENV gate on `app/rewards/login/LoginForm.tsx` `[rewards-login] demo code: ${data.demoCode}` console.log. Pre-fix relied SOLELY on server-side gating (server only emits demoCode when SMS is unconfigured). If a server-side regression ever emitted demoCode in prod (env-var typo, Twilio outage during the request, key-rotation race during a reload), the OTP would silently leak into the customer's browser console — visible to browser extensions, shoulder-surfers on shared screens, screen-recording tools, browser-DevTools-pasted screen-shares to support staff, etc. Post-fix: gate also on `process.env.NODE_ENV !== "production"` so prod literally cannot log it even if the data branch fires. Audit lens (`grep -rEn 'console\\.log\\(' --include='*.tsx' --include='*.ts' app components lib`) found this as scc's lone non-cron console.log site. tsc clean.
// 11.305 — 🛡️ saveCart() iOS-Safari-private wrap — `app/order/OrderMenu.tsx:61-69` `saveCart()` was calling `localStorage.setItem("sc_cart", JSON.stringify(payload))` UNWRAPPED. Sister of glw v10.305 (this push's glw sister) + inv v363.005/v368.405 + scc v11.205 (which wrapped only AddToHomeScreen sites — missed saveCart). iOS Safari private mode + iOS quota-exceeded both throw on setItem; the throw bubbled out of saveCart() (called from cart-mutation handlers) → React click handler → error boundary trip → cart UI tanked mid-add with no recovery short of full reload. The READ side loadCart() at line 51-59 was already wrapped; this was the missing WRITE-side sister. Worst-case impact: customer adds 5 items at lunch break, locks phone, comes back, cart empty AND first add error-boundary-trips. tsc clean.
